author: Brian Josephs
title: Todd Gurley Flipped the Hell Out of Clay Matthews During a Blitz
text:
It's not a shock that Clay Matthews felt comfortable blitzing with the way he broke Nick Foles . Rather than ineptitude, we'll assume that the Rams simply forgot they had to look for Matthews at all times.
And everybody knows that if you get good ribs, you want more of it. But rookie Todd Gurley said, "No more." Matthews made the crazy to decision to leap over protection. As a result, Matthews landed on his head thanks to Gurley's patented powerbomb GurleyBomb.
Gurley is not a bust.
[ via Nick Amato ]
